# @no-proxy

### Auth Endpoints
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@token = your_jwt_token_here
@msToken = your_microsoft_access_token_here

# User IDs (update after creating users and logging in)
@aliceId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@bobId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002
@carolId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003
@davidId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004
@evaId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005
@frankId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006
@graceId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000007
@henryId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000008
@ivyId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000009
@jackId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/../health

### ========== Create 10 Sample Users ==========

### Register User 1 - Alice Johnson (Engineering)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice.johnson@company.com",
  "full_name": "Alice Johnson",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}
========== Login Examples ==========

### Login as Alice
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice.johnson@company.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

### Login as Bob
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob.smith@company.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

### Login as Carol
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "carol.white@company
  "email": "bob.smith@company.com",
  "full_name": "Bob Smith",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

